   and Garribba, Eugenio and Bauza, Antonio and Frontera, Antonio and
   Pilet, Guillaume and Mitra, Samiran},
Title = {{Magneto-structural and theoretical study of the weak interactions in a
   Mn(II) complex with a very unusual N,O-chelating coordination mode of
   2-aminoterephthalate}},
Journal = {{INORGANICA CHIMICA ACTA}},
Year = {{2017}},
Volume = {{461}},
Pages = {{183-191}},
Month = {{MAY 1}},
Abstract = {{The Mn(II) complex \{{[}Mn(atpa)(H2O)(2)]center dot H2O\} n (1), with
   the dicarboxylate ligand 2- aminoterephthalic acid (H2atpa), has been
   synthesized and crystallographically, spectroscopically and magnetically
   characterized. Complex 1 shows a very unusual 1 kappa N-2, O
   coordination mode of the aminoterephthalate dianion with the Mn(II) ion.
   One of the carboxylate groups shows a syn-anti- mu(2)- eta(1): eta(1)
   binding mode to form a 2D square grid. The magnetic properties of this
   compound can be very well reproduced with a regular S = 5/2 chain model
   with a very weak antiferromagnetic coupling constant of J = -0.2 cm(-1)
   through the single syn- anti carboxylate bridges. EPR measurement also
   supports the experimental data obtained from the magnetic study. The
   influence of the torsion angle between the carboxylate groups on the
   various interaction energies of 1 is calculated by means of DFT study.
   (C) 2017 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.}},
