Abstract = {{This work presents the successful CVD heteroepitaxial growth of 3C-SiC
   on diamond (100) substrates. When performing a direct SiC growth at 1500
   degrees C on such substrate, it leads to polycrystalline deposit. The
   use of a substrate pretreatment involving silicon deposition allows
   forming a more continuous and smoother layer. Electron BackScatter
   Diffraction and Transmission Electron Microscopy all revealed that the
   3C-SiC layer grown on the (100) diamond substrate is monocrystalline and
   well oriented.}},
