Note = {{39th Edition of the Joint European Days on Equilibrium between Phases
   (JEEP), Nancy, FRANCE, MAR 19-21, 2013}},
Abstract = {{Low aqueous solubilities are data of great importance in both industrial
   and environmental fields. As for the low aqueous solubility, we present
   the experimental apparatus along with the optimizations and adjustments
   (mechanical and analytical) applied to measure the solubility of heavy
   polyaromtics (solubility down to 10(-9) in molal). The validation of our
   apparatus was achieved by measuring the aqueous solubility of the
   Fluoranthene in a range between 298.15 and 338.15 K. The quantification
   was done using GC-MS SIM with internal calibration method with benzo(a)
   pyrene as internal standard. Solubility of dibenz(a, c) anthracene was
   then explored between 298 and 333 K with an extremely low solubility of
   10(-12) in molar fraction.}},
