   (ICSCRM 2011), Cleveland, OH, SEP 11-16, 2011}},
Organization = {{Cree; Keithley Instruments; AIXTRON; Dow Corn Elect Solut; Gen Elect;
   CuttingEdgeIons com; Off Naval Res Global; NASA Glenn Res Ctr; Infineon;
   SemiSouth; Microsemi; OAI}},
Abstract = {{In this work we report on SiC epitaxial growth by vapour-liquid-solid
   (VLS) mechanism on on-axis 4H-SiC(0001) substrates which were previously
   patterned to form mesa structures. The liquid phase was set to Al70Si30.
   At 1100 degrees C, it led to very high homoepitaxial lateral growth (140
   pm/h) with pronounced spiral growth and in plane anisotropy of growth
   rate. Upon temperature increase to 1200 degrees C, this spiral growth
   was suppressed and the lateral growth was further increased up to 180 mu
   m/h. The in-plane versus out-of-plane anisotropy of growth rate was
   found to be as high as 60 at this temperature and 46 at 1100 degrees C.}},
