Abstract = {{We report on n-type 3C-SiC samples grown by sublimation epitaxy. We
   focus on the low temperature photoluminescence intensity and show that
   the presence of a first conversion layer, grown at low temperature, is
   not only beneficial to improve the homogeneity of the polytype
   conversion but, also, to the LTPL signal intensity. From the use of a
   simple model, we show that this comes from a reduced density of
   non-radiative recombination centers.}},
