   ENSICAEN; USEK; Univ Libanaise; Agence Univ Francophonie; Amer Univ
   Beirut; Univ St Joseph; Beirut Arab Univ}},
Abstract = {{In this work, the capability of the proton Induced gamma-ray Emission
   (PIGE) technique to monitor a rapid, nondestructive and quantification
   of Boron in ultra-thin films of BxGa1-xAs deposited on GaAs substrate
   using MOCVD is discussed. In order to improve the sensitivity for B
   detection, a systematic study was undertaken using proton induced beam
   at three different energies (from 1.7, 2.4 and 3 MeV) with different
   tilting angles (0, 60 degrees and 80 degrees). Best conditions were
   found to be at 1.7 MeV and at 80 degrees for proton energy and tilting
   angle within ten minutes of acquisition time.}},
